  "body": "**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\n\r\n1. Right now `processInactivityUpdates` takes the same amount of time to `processRewardsAndPenalties`, and all of the time is for the loop not for the update itself\r\n```\r\nSep-15 08:25:18.745 []                 info: Syncing - 16 minutes left - 2.55 slots/s - head: 1260909 0x6d2a…7479 - finalized: 1260832 0x9238…3285 (39401) - clockSlot: 1263426 - peers: 3\r\n@@@ processInactivityUpdates for epoch 39403 in 108 num change 0\r\n@@@ processRewardsAndPenalties for epoch 39403 in 120\r\n@@@ processInactivityUpdates for epoch 39404 in 106 num change 0\r\n@@@ processRewardsAndPenalties for epoch 39404 in 111\r\n```\r\nthis is due to `FLAG_ELIGIBLE_ATTESTER` being imported\r\n\r\n![Screen Shot 2021-09-15 at 08 25 37](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10568965/133355931-3f93edb2-2599-4302-9d6a-872647a02eda.png)\r\n\r\n2. When we have to process empty epoch, it's likely that we have to update `inactivityScore` for all validators and it makes the function run like crazy\r\n![Screen Shot 2021-09-15 at 08 48 19](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10568965/133357133-d8b975da-b244-4d39-b85a-3cfe22ae75fe.png)\r\n\r\nthe above profile was taken when we have OOM issue (node is almost synced to head), the whole epoch transition takes > 11s, most of that is for `processInactivityUpdates` (`processRewardsAndPenalties` takes only 700ms in this case) \r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\n\r\n1. this is due to the way `tsc` compiles our code to always import inline\r\n```\r\nif ((0, util_1.hasMarkers)(status.flags, util_1.FLAG_ELIGIBLE_ATTESTER)) {\r\n```\r\nwe should find a way to import that only 1 time, or redefine the constant\r\n\r\n2. If we have to update all `inactivityScores` we should rebuild the whole tree (similar to `balances.UpdateAll`) instead of doing individual updates. The worse performance of this function should be close to `processRewardsAndPenalties` where we rebuild the whole tree. \r\n",
